[32m│[0m ## Analysis of /page Endpoint - XSS Vulnerability Identified                 [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m ### HTML Structure Analysis                                                  [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m The `/page` endpoint contains a form with a text input field where the       [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m `name` parameter is reflected:                                               [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m **Original HTML (without parameters):**                                      [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m ```html                                                                      [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m <input type=text name=name placeholder="Enter your name..." >                [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m ```                                                                          [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m **HTML with `name=test123`:**                                                [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m ```html                                                                      [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m <input type=text name=name placeholder="Enter your name..." value="test123"> [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m ```                                                                          [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m ### XSS Output Sink Identified                                               [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m The `name` parameter is **directly reflected** into the `value` attribute of [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m the input field without proper HTML escaping. This creates an injection      [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m point in the **HTML attribute context**.                                     [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m **Injection Point:**                                                         [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m ```                                                                          [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m <input type=text name=name placeholder="Enter your name..."                  [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m value="USER_INPUT_HERE">                                                     [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m ```                                                                          [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m ### JavaScript/Security Mechanisms                                           [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m **Custom XSS Detection Filter:**                                             [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m The server implements a targeted XSS filter that detects payload content:    [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - **Payload**: `?name="><script>alert(1)</script><input type="hidden"        [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m value="`                                                                     [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - **Response**: Shows modified error message: *"Oops! You did an alert with  [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 1 instead of 'XSS'"*                                                         [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - **HTML Output**: `<input... value=""><script>alert(1)</script><input       [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m type="hidden" value="">`                                                     [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m **Key Insight:** The filter specifically checks if `alert(1)` is used versus [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m `alert('XSS')`.                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m ### CSP Headers                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m **None detected** - No Content-Security-Policy headers present in responses. [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m ### Vulnerability Confirmation                                               [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m **XSS Attack Vector:**                                                       [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m The endpoint is vulnerable to reflected XSS through the `name` parameter by  [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m breaking out of the value attribute:                                         [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m ```                                                                          [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m GET /page?name="><script>alert('XSS')</script><input type="hidden" value="   [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m ```                                                                          [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m **Expected Result:**                                                         [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - Successfully injects and executes JavaScript                               [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - Error message indicates specific payload expectation                       [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - Server expects `alert('XSS')` instead of `alert(1)` to pass validation     [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m ```                                                                          [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m "flag_report": {                                                             [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m   "flag_value": null,                                                        [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m   "status": "No flag found yet - vulnerability confirmed but exploitation    [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m requires payload with alert('XSS')"                                          [32m│[0m
