[32m│[0m ## XSS Sink Analysis Results                                                 [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m Based on systematic testing with unique markers, here are the identified XSS [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m output sinks:                                                                [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m ### **Primary XSS Sink: `/page` endpoint**                                   [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m **Reflection Point**: GET parameter `name`                                   [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m **Context**: HTML attribute (input value)                                    [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m **Evidence**:                                                                [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m ```html                                                                      [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m <input type=text name=name placeholder="Enter your name..."                  [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m value="SINK_TEST_12345">                                                     [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m ```                                                                          [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m **Detailed Summary**:                                                        [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - The `/page` endpoint reflects the `name` parameter value directly into the [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m HTML input tag's `value` attribute                                           [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - The marker `SINK_TEST_12345` appears verbatim in the attribute context     [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - This represents a classic reflected XSS vulnerability in an HTML attribute [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m context                                                                      [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - No URL encoding or HTML escaping is applied to the reflected value         [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m ### **Endpoint `/` analysis**                                                [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m **Finding**: No reflections detected                                         [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - GET parameters are not processed (tested with `?test=SINK_TEST_12345`)     [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - Common headers are not reflected (tested User-Agent and Referer with       [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m markers)                                                                     [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - Response remains static regardless of input                                [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m ### **Vulnerability Assessment**                                             [32m│[0m
